BACKTAB~

________________________________________

BACKTAB moves the cursor left to the
previous tab stop on the current line.
_______________________________________

Tab stops are initially set at every 8 columns beginning after
column 1 (that is, at 9, 17, 25, 33, 41, 49, and so on).  You can
redefine the tab settings with the SET TABS command.

To see the tab settings, use the ?  TABS command on the command
line.

See also TAB, BACKTAB WORD, TAB WORD, SET TABS, SET HSCROLL,
? TABS, and ? HSCROLL.







BACKTAB WORD~

________________________________________

BACKTAB WORD moves the cursor backwards
through the file to the first character
of the previous word.
________________________________________

A word is defined to be a group of characters separated by
blanks.

The cursor skips back to a lower number line, if necessary.

See also TAB WORD, BACKTAB, and TAB.





