BEGIN MARK~

________________________________________

BEGIN MARK moves the cursor to the
beginning of the current marked area, if
any.
________________________________________

The marked area may be in a file other than the current file.

For line marks, the cursor column is not changed.  For character
and block marks, the cursor moves to the far left marked
character on the first line of the marked area.

You can use the BEGIN MARK and END MARK commands as search
markers.  If you mark a character (line or block) in a file to
which you often refer, you can edit other files and then return
to the marked file by using BEGIN MARK.

See also END MARK.


