BEGIN WORD~

________________________________________

BEGIN WORD moves the cursor to the first
character of the word where it is now
located.
________________________________________

If the cursor is not within a word, the cursor moves to the first
character of the word to the left of the cursor.

If there is no word to the left of the cursor, the cursor moves
to the first character of the first word on the current line.

See also END WORD, TAB WORD, and BACKTAB WORD.







BOTTOM~

________________________________________

BOTTOM moves the cursor to the last line
of the current file.
_______________________________________

The column the cursor is in does not change.

See also TOP and LINE.







BOTTOM EDGE~

________________________________________

BOTTOM EDGE moves the cursor to the last
line of the text area of the current
window.
________________________________________

The column the cursor is in does not change.

The cursor moves down and the contents of the current window do
not change.

See also TOP EDGE.


