SET TABS~

________________________________________

SET TABS changes the tab markers from
the current setting.
________________________________________

Format:  set tabs t1 t2 t3 t4 ... t20

You can assign 20 tabs to a file between column 1 and 255.

The numbers must follow in increasing order.  The second number
has to be larger than the first, and the third larger than the
second, and so on.

PE II starts with tab settings every eight spaces, starting at 9,
17, 25, and so on, unless reset in the profile.  To change the
tabs, type the SET TABS command and the tab numbers on the
command line and press Enter.

Example:  set tabs 5 10 15 20

To see the current tab settings, enter ? TABS on the command
line.

When you use the EDIT command to create a new file or display an
old one, the tab settings for that file are the tab settings for
whatever file was on the screen when you typed the EDIT command.

You cannot save the tab settings of a file.  They have to be
reset each time you start PE II.

This command controls the tab settings used by the TAB and
BACKTAB commands, but not the  ab positions used by blank
compression and tab expansion by the EDIT, FILE, and SAVE
commands.  The latter tab positions are fixed at every eight
columns beginning at column 9.

See also ? TABS, BACKTAB, BACKTAB WORD, and TAB.





