SPLIT~

________________________________________

SPLIT divides the current line at the
cursor into two lines.
________________________________________

SPLIT divides the current line into two lines.  Text before the
cursor on the current line remains on that line and text at or
past the cursor is moved to a newly inserted line beginning at
column one.

The only way to insert a line before the beginning of the file is
to use SPLIT when the cursor is in the first column of the file.

See also JOIN.







SPLIT SCREEN~

________________________________________

SPLIT SCREEN divides the screen into
two or four windows.
________________________________________

The screen can be divided horizontally or vertically into either
two or four windows.

There are four possible divisions of the screen into windows:

o  The entire screen as one window

o  The screen split vertically into two windows

o  The screen split vertically and horizontally into four windows

o  The screen split horizontally into two windows

SPLIT SCREEN cycles through these four divisions in the above
order.

See also NEXT VIEW, NEXT WINDOW, and ZOOM WINDOW.


