TAB~

________________________________________

TAB moves the cursor right to the next
tab stop.
________________________________________

Tab stops are originally set at every 8 columns beginning after
column 1 at column 9, 17, 25, 33, 41, 49, and so on.  You can
also redefine the tab settings with the SET TABS command.

To see the tab settings, use the ? TABS command.

See also BACKTAB, BACKTAB WORD, TAB WORD, SET TABS, and ? TABS.






TAB WORD~

________________________________________

TAB WORD moves the cursor to the right,
stopping at the first character in the
next word.
________________________________________


A word is defined to be a group of nonblank characters separated
by blanks.

The cursor skips forward to higher numbered lines, if necessary.

See also TAB, BACKTAB, and BACKTAB WORD.






TOP~

________________________________________

TOP moves the cursor to the first line
of the current file.
________________________________________

The column of the cursor does not change.

See also BOTTOM and LINE.


