TOP EDGE~

________________________________________

TOP EDGE moves the cursor to the top
line of the text area of the current
window.
________________________________________

The column of the cursor does not change.

The cursor moves up, and the contents of the current window do
not change.

See also BOTTOM EDGE.






UNDO~

_______________________________________

UNDO restores the current line to what
was there the last time the cursor
moved onto the line.
_______________________________________

UNDO recovers erased lines or words as long as the cursor had not
left the current line before the change was made.  Once the
cursor leaves the line or joins two lines, you cannot restore
that line.

If the cursor has left the line, you can retrieve the last five
changes from the .UNNAMED internal file.  To see the .UNNAMED
file, on the command line enter: e .unnamed

See also EDIT.





